<b>Subject:</b> Re: Outstanding PvP Issues - are we in agreement?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2062" TARGET=_self>Outstanding PvP Issues - are we in agreement?</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I agree with it all except the looting of backpacks... that just puts us Warrior types (even Shaman are warrior types) at a bigger disadvantage, since now we would be even bigger goldmines (i.e. we couldn't sack away our most valuable loot). Lootable bags wouldn't affect a Caster in any way... the only thing they lose was something they found on a monster or something they looted off a warrior.

<P>Funny with the /d thing... the only people who thought it wasn't a problem were those that actively pulled the cheap stunt. Interesting justifications they came up with tho.
<P>Holly.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
